$ Windows Server

Windows Server allows multiple → Windows/Remote-Desktop-Services#rds-rdc[remote desktop connections] at a time.
(→ Windows/versions/10 only allows one at a time).

{ Identifying a Windows Server

  Windows Server can be distinguished from a Windows Client by the value of
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Control/ProductOptions#ProductType[`ProductType`] in the
  → Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key]
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Control/ProductOptions[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\ProductOptions`].

}
